All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    Atom
    A basic structure only defined by its name, its description, its id, its type and by an optional alias which can be used for a synonym of name.
    Field
    A field is defined within a record by its starting position and its length or by its starting and ending positions.
    FieldClass
    The list of internal possible field classes.
    FieldType
    Each field within a record-oriented file has a type, which is defined in the XML layout file and associated with each field.
    Layout
    A layout is the description of the structure of a record-oriented file.
    Reader
    Allow to iterate through all records of a record-oriented file.
    Reader.RecordMapper
    The function type to map a line read from the input file into a record name
    Record
    A record is a list of fields, which are not necessarly contiguous.
